HEADWORD: Subtilism
<hw>Sub"til*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being subtile; subtility; subtlety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The high orthodox <qex>subtilism</qex> of Duns Scotus.</q>
